    "note": "Constants are mathematically derived (not empirical): SHA-256 K = cube roots of primes, Blowfish P = pi hex expansion, XTEA delta = golden ratio * 2^32, MD5 T = floor(abs(sin(i+1)) * 2^32) Single-byte and small (<0x10000) constants removed to prevent false positives; their algorithms are detected via full S-box sequences instead."
